nt` job in python-lint.yml\n193:   - Job ID: `python_lint`\n194:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n195:   - Verify: Job defined\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T6.4** Add paths-filter for Python code changes\n198:   - Filter ID: `python`\n199:   - Paths: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n200:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n201:   - Verify: Path filter detects Python-related changes\n202: \n203: - [ ] **T6.5** Add Python 3.10 setup step\n204:   - Use: `actions/setup-python@v5` with `python-version: '3.10'`\n205:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n206:   - Verify: Python 3.10 installed\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T6.6** Add Ruff installation step\n209:   - Run: `pip install ruff`\n210:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n211:   - Verify: Ruff installed\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T6.7** Add Ruff check execution step\n214:   - Run: `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n215:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n216:   - Working directory: repository root\n217:   - Verify: Ruff linting runs from repo root\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Phase 7: Test Coverage Workflow (test-coverage.yml)\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T7.1** Create `test-coverage.yml` workflow file\n224:   - File: `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml`\n225:   - Name: `Test Coverage`\n226:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T7.2** Define triggers for test-coverage.yml\n229:   - Trigger: `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call`\n230:   - Verify: All three trigger types configured\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T7.3** Add workflow_call inputs for CODECOV_TOKEN\n233:   - Input: `CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional, string)\n234:   - Verify: Token can be passed from reusable workflows\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T7.4** Create `coverage` job in test-coverage.yml\n237:   - Job ID: `coverage`\n238:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n239:   - Verify: Job defined\n240: \n241: - [ ] **T7.5** Add paths-filter for coverage\n242:   - Filter ID: `coverage`\n243:   - Paths: `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n244:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n245:   - Verify: Path filter excludes non-code files\n246: \n247: - [ ] **T7.6** Add free disk space step\n248:   - Run: Disk cleanup commands for runner\n249:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n250:   - Verify: More disk space available for Go modules\n251: \n252: - [ ] **T7.7** Add Go 1.24 setup step\n253:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24'`\n254:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n255:   - Verify: Go 1.24 installed\n256: \n257: - [ ] **T7.8** Add go test with coverage step\n258:   - Run: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n259:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n260:   - Verify: Coverage report generated\n261: \n262: - [ ] **T7.9** Add coverage summary to GitHub step summary\n263:   - Run: Generate coverage percentage and write to `$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY`\n264:   - Verify: Coverage displayed in workflow UI\n265: \n266: - [ ] **T7.10** Add Codecov upload step\n267:   - Use: `codecov/codecov-action@v4`\n268:   - With: `token: ${{ secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN }}`, `files: coverage.out`\n269:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true' && secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN != ''`\n270:   - Verify: Coverage uploaded to Codecov when token available\n271: \n272: - [ ] **T7.11** Add coverage artifact upload step\n273:   - Use: `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with name `go-coverage`, path `coverage.out`\n274:   - Verify: Coverage file available as artifact\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Phase 8: Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `codegen-check.yml` workflow file\n281:   - File: `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml`\n282:   - Name: `Codegen Check`\n283:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n284: \n285: - [ ] **T8.2** Define pull_request triggers